==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[woolly]] (''British'')

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|wooli|er}}

# Made of [[wool]].
# Having a thick, soft texture, as if made of wool.
#:''wooly hair''
# (''figurative'') Of thinking, principles, etc, based on emotion rather than logic.
#:''That's the sort of '''wooly''' thinking that causes wars to start.''

====Related terms====
*[[wooly-minded]] ''(US)'', [[woolly-minded]] (''British'')

===Etymology===
From ''[[woolyback]]''

====Noun====
{{en-noun|wool|ies}}

# {{cattag|British|slang}} Someone not born in [[Liverpool]] (especially from the towns of Wigan, St Helen's, Widnes, Warrington and Runcorn).

